  "img": "systems/n5eb/assets/Icons%20%26%20Images/Clans/Claymore.png",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You prefer to travel light, and your choice of armor reflects this. Starting at 7th level, while you are wearing light or medium armor, your movement speed is increased by +10 feet, and you gain a +1d4 bonus to Acrobatics and Athletics checks.</p><p>Additionally, you have completely replaced the material that your armor is made out of with the same material as your sword, making it unbreakable. While you are wearing light or medium armor, you gain advantage on saving throws made to resist Mental conditions.</p><p>Finally, twice per rest, when you would fail a saving throw, you can add your Taijutsu Ability Modifier to the final result.</p><p>Starting at 11th level, you ignore disadvantage imposed by hostile creatures for making saving throws or contested ability or skill checks.</p><p>Additionally, once per long rest, when you would fall to or below 0 hit points or be subjected to an instant death effect, you are instead reduced to 1 hit point and gain advantage on all death saving throws made in the next minute.</p>",
